com.solacesystems.jcsmp

Interface SDTMap


  • public interface SDTMap
    Map Structured Data Type (SDT) that maps case-sensitive Strings to a supported data type. The list of supported data types are:
    • Boolean,
    • Byte,
    • byte[],
    • Character,
    • Destination,
    • Double,
    • Float,
    • Integer,
    • Long,
    • SDTMap,
    • Short,
    • SDTStream,
    • String.

    For values written as the row type, they can be read as the column type according to the following table. 

     |        | boolean byte byte[] char dest double float int long Map  short Stream String 
 |--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 |boolean |    X                                                                    X
 |byte    |          X                                  X   X          X            X
 |byte[]  |                X
 |char    |                      X                                                  X
 |dest    |                           X
 |double  |                                 X                                       X
 |float   |                                 X      X                                X
 |int     |          X                                  X   X          X            X
 |long    |          X                                  X   X          X            X
 |Map     |                                                      X
 |SMFMsg  |                                                          
 |short   |          X                                  X   X          X            X
 |Stream  |                                                                  X
 |String  |    X     X                      X      X    X   X          X            X 
 |--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    A SDTMap may not contain itself as a value.

        Object get(String key)
    throws SDTException
        Returns the value mapped to the specified case-sensitive key. If null is returned, it may mean that the specified mapping does not exist, or that the key is mapped to null. Use containsKey to distinguish the two cases.
        Parameters:
        key - The case-sensitive key of the mapping value to return.
        Returns:
        Returns the value mapped to the specified key.
        Throws:
        SDTException - Thrown if an internal error occurs accessing the map.

      • getMap

        SDTMap getMap(String key)
       throws SDTException
        Returns the SDTMap value mapped to the specified case-sensitive key. If null is returned, it might mean that the specified mapping does not exist, or that the key is mapped to null. Use containsKey to distinguish the two cases.

        The returned SDTMap is backed by this SDTMap, so changes to it will modify the SDTMap.

        Parameters:
        key - The case-sensitive key of the mapping value to return.
        Returns:
        Returns the value mapped to the specified key.
        Throws:
        SDTException - Thrown if an internal error occurs accessing the map.
        SDTFormatException - If the conversion from the mapped type to a SDTMap is invalid.

      • putBoolean

        void putBoolean(String key,
                Boolean value)
         throws SDTException
        Associates the specified case-sensitive key with the value in the map. If there is a mapping with this key already the value is replaced. The value can be null.
        Parameters:
        key - The case-sensitive key that the value is associated with.
        value - The value to associate with the specified key.
        Throws:
        SDTException - Thrown if an internal error occurs accessing the map
        IllegalArgumentException - if the key is null or an empty string.

        void putBytes(String key,
              byte[] value)
       throws SDTException
        Associates the specified case-sensitive key with the value in the map. If there is a mapping with this key already the value is replaced. The value can be null. A reference to the byte[] argument is stored so any changes to the argument byte[] will be reflected when getting the byte[].

        key - The case-sensitive key that the value is associated with.
        value - The value to associate with the specified key.
        Throws:
        SDTException - Thrown if an internal error occurs accessing the map
        IllegalArgumentException - if the key is null or an empty string.

      • putAll

        void putAll(SDTMap map)
     throws SDTException
        Copies the mappings from the given SDTMap and puts them in this SDTMap. This is equivalent to calling put(String key, Object value) on all the mappings.
        Parameters:
        map - SDTMap with the mappings to add.
        Throws:
        SDTException - Thrown if an internal error occurs accessing the map.
